frus:attachment.p:
Considering, that in order to fulfill the purposes of the treaty concluded
                        between Haiti and the United States on September 16, 1915, a protocol was
                        concluded between the two Governments on October 3, 1919;

Considering, that in an exchange of notes between the two Governments,
                        certain modifications of the protocol were accepted and confirmed in the
                        notes of the 1st and 3rd of June, 1922;

Considering, that in order to arrive at a revision of the customs tariff and
                        to diminish the taxes actually borne by the mass of the people, it is
                        necessary to release the public revenues from the pledges now existing;
